                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Article from the “Morning Post” January 18, 1916</hi>
                    </head>
                    <p rend="center">THE BLOCKADE FARCE</p>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Increase in Germany’s Imports—The Navy Crippled by
                            Foreign Office—Startling American Trade Figures</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>In order that the full significance of the figures given below by our
                        Washington correspondent may be the better appreciated we give them in
                        tabular form. The quantities are for the first ten months of 1913 and the
                        corresponding period of 1915:</p>
